<topic template="Default" status="Needs Review" lasteditedby="lgisaacs" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Staff</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Staff</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Header 2" style="text-align:right;"><link displaytype="image" src="New_Back_Arrow_icon.gif" type="topiclink" href="Support"></link><text styleclass="Header 2" style="font-size:8pt;" translate="true">&#32;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Support" styleclass="Answer" style="font-size:8pt;" translate="true">Return to Support Menu</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[How do I add a new user to the system?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">In order to add new staff members to the system please follow the directions listed below. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Only certain user types have access to add new staff members, if you do not see any of the menu options listed in the directions below please contact your district administrator:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="11" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Add</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Fill in the desired </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">profile</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> information for the new staff member:</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:96px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">LoginID</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:96px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">User Name</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:96px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">Email (optional)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:96px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">School</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:96px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">User Type</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:96px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">Restrictions (refer to step 4)</text></para>
          <list id="11" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Change the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">restrictions</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> drop down to </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">change password on next login</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">This means that the first time the user signs in they will be prompted to change their password.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Reset</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Password</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">. Choose a password for the user to use on the initial log in.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.0;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[How do I edit a user that is already in the system?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">In order to edit a user that is already in the system please follow the directions listed below. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Only certain user types have access to edit new staff members, if you do not see any of the menu options listed in the directions below please contact your district administrator:</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="12" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">. </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Use the search criteria on the Find Staff - Search Criteria screen to locate the user. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">If the user you are editing is a teacher but currently has no classes in Elements you will need to choose &quot;Teacher&quot; in the user type drop down then change the Status drop down to &quot;All Years&quot;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:96px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Name</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:96px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">User Type</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:96px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">UserID</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:96px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Cluster</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:96px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">SchoolType</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:96px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">School</text></para>
          <list id="12" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Select</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">edit</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> next to the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Once the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">USER</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">: </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Profile</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> screen opens you can make any changes to the user information you desire. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Please note that changes to LoginID&apos;s and User Names could cause potential duplicate user creation when roster files are imported. &#160;Any changes made in Elements needs to be reflected in your Information System.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[What are the different user types and what is the difference?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">The 4 default user types are Tmanager, Cmanager, Administrator and Teacher. &#160;Listed below are the default restrictions and permissions for the different user types. &#160;If your district uses customer user types then many of these restrictions could be different. &#160;You will need to contact your district administrator or Thinkgate Support (if permitted) for more information. &#160;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="13" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Tmanager</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> - </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Tmanagers</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> are the least restricted, highest user type in a system. &#160;The tmanager user type is usually reserved for the Primary Point and Data Contact in a district. &#160;Tmanagers have access to all modules purchased by a district as well as the ability to upload files to Thinkgate Support. &#160;Tmanager do not have any school restrictions. </text><br/></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Cmanagers</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> - Cmanagers are the second highest user type. &#160;They have all the same access as the tmanager minus the ability to upload files to Thinkgate Support. &#160;By default, cmanagers have no school restrictions. &#160;This user type is usually reserved for a district&apos;s assessment building team or permitted users needing to run district wide reports.</text><br/></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Administrators</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> - Adminstrators are the &quot;read only&quot; user type in Elements. &#160;They are restricted to their respective school and can report on any data at the school level. &#160;This user type is usually restricted for principals at individual schools who only need to run reports on their school. </text><br/></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Teachers</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> - The teacher user type is unique in Elements due to the fact that all criteria is controlled by a class and curriculum drop down in the left nav. &#160;A teacher can only see data based on the classes they are tied to. &#160;They control which class they want to look at by manipulating the two drop downs in their left nav. &#160;Teachers do not have access to any school or district information.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can I create custom user types?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Yes, a district has the option to create custom user types or can request specific permissions for a user type that is already available in Elements. &#160;If custom users need to be created please contact your district administrator or Thinkgate Support.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can I change a user's user type after they are added to the system?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Yes, once a user has been added to the system their user type can be changed at any time. &#160;This can only be done by tmanager or cmanagers. &#160;Please follow the steps below to change a user&apos;s user type:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="14" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Enter the criteria to search for the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Edit</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> for the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Use the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">User</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Type</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> drop down to select a new user type for the user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can a user be deleted from the system?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Yes, a user can be deleted from the system. </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true"> However, in the case of teachers, if they have any current or prior year classes or data tied to them they cannot be deleted. &#160;If a teacher leaves the school but has historical data they must remain in the system. &#160;This is due to prior year reporting purposes. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true">In order to delete a user from the system please follow the directions listed below:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="15" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Enter the criteria to search for the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Edit</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> for the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Delete</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> in the left nav</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can I lock a user out of the system without deleting them?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Yes, a user can be locked out of the system by revoking their access. &#160;In order to revoke a user&apos;s access follow these steps </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">(only tmanagers and cmanagers can revoke a user)</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="16" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Enter the criteria to search for the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Edit</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> for the desired user</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Change the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Restrictions</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> drop down to </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Access Revoked</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Save</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Once a user is set to </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Access Revoked</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> they will be unable to log into the system. &#160;The revoked status can be removed at anytime.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[I just added a new user, however, they are not showing when I search for them.  Why?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">When a teacher has been added but cannot be located it is normally due to the status drop down in the search criteria being set to current year. &#160;Teachers who do not have current year classes can be found by changing this drop down to </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">All Years</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">. &#160;In order to make this change follow these steps:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="17" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select &#160;the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Use the criteria to search for the desired user. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">Make sure you change the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">User</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Type</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> drop down to </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Teachers</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">, this will give you access to the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Status</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> drop down. &#160;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">Change the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:normal;" translate="true">Status</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true"> drop down to </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:normal;" translate="true">All Years</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Select </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find Staff</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">The teacher should now be included in the list. &#160;New teachers will also show up in the list if the user type is set to all because under this option there is no Status drop down.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[When a teacher signs in they do not see any classes, why?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">There are two possible issues if a teacher logs in and does not see any classes. &#160;</text></para>
          <list id="18" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:24px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">The</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> teacher is not assigned to any classes. &#160;If a teacher is manually added then not associated with any classes they will not see any drop downs when they log in. &#160;</text><br/></li>
          </list>
          <list id="19" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:24px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">A </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">duplicate</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true"> user was created, either manually or through a roster import. &#160;If a teacher has a duplicate user then one user will usually have the classes and the other will not. &#160;In order to check if a teacher has a duplicate user, follow these steps:</text></li>
          </list>
          <list id="20" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Support</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Choose the </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">icon</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Use the criteria to search for the desired user. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Try be use the least amount of criteria possible, for example, only the last name or first three letters of last name.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Find</text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Staff</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">If a user has duplicate logins you should see their name twice in the resulting list (or some form of their name). &#160;If you see duplicate users you will need to contact your district administrator or Thinkgate Support (if permitted).</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[How are duplicate users created?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">There are two ways a duplicate user can be created. &#160;Either through manually adding a user or a roster import.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer"></para>
          <list id="21" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000080;">
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">If a user is manually added with a different name, loginID, school, etc. then their record in the district&apos;s Information System then when a file is imported a duplicate user will be created.</text><br/></li>
            <li styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"><text styleclass="Answer" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">If a user&apos;s </text><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">record in a roster file changes between two different files, for example, new school, last name, first name, user id, etc. (and teacher ID&apos;s are not included) then a duplicate will be created.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:48px;"></para>
          <para styleclass="Answer" style="margin-left:0px;"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">The best way to prevent duplicate users from being created is to include a Teacher ID column in the roster file. &#160;This teacher ID can be used as a unique identifier for every teacher and can be used as a cross reference to update existing teacher records. &#160;In the case of manually added staff, the manually added user needs to be deleted since, more than likely, classes will be associated with the other user. &#160;If you run into any issues with duplicate users, or see a lot of them in your system, contact your district administrator or Thinkgate Support (if permitted).</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Normal"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="hmtoggle_plus0.gif" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Normal"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[What do I do if I see duplicate users?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:42px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Answer"><text styleclass="Answer" translate="true">If you find duplicate users in your system please contact your district administrator or Thinkgate Support (if permitted).</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
